This pull request includes several updates to the ALCF/examples/finetune_llama3 directory, focusing on enhancing the setup, configuration, and logging for fine-tuning Llama models. The key changes include adding a detailed README for setup instructions, updating configuration files, and improving logging and environment setup in the scripts. Documentation: ALCF/examples/finetune_llama3/README.md : Added detailed setup instructions for fine-tuning Llama3 from a Hugging Face checkpoint, including cloning the repository, setting up the environment, installing dependencies, downloading data, and converting checkpoints. Configuration: ALCF/examples/finetune_llama3/ds_config.json and ALCF/examples/finetune_llama3/ds_config_empty.json : Added configuration files for DeepSpeed, specifying training batch sizes, optimizer settings, and bf16 optimization. [1] [2] Scripts: ALCF/examples/finetune_llama3/finetune_llama.sh : Enhanced the script to include environment setup, dataset download, model configuration, and command execution for converting and fine-tuning models. Logging and Environment: finetune_llama.py : Integrated ezpz for environment setup and logging, added support for Weights & Biases (W&B) logging, and replaced print_rank_0 with logger.info . [1] [2] [3] [4] [5] megatron/data/prompt_dataset.py : Updated to use ezpz for logging instead of the standard logging module. [1] [2]
These changes collectively improve the usability, configuration, and logging of the fine-tuning process for Llama models.
